  "raw_html": "<button type='button' role='link' class='btn btn-link p-0 text-start' id='link_4' aria-label=\" Kabir Paharia versus National Medical Commission and Others pdf\"  class='noToken' href='#' onclick=javascript:open_pdf('4','2025','2025_5_653_666','2025INSC623'); ><font size='4'> <strong>KABIR PAHARIA<span class='fst-italic'> versus </span>NATIONAL MEDICAL COMMISSION AND OTHERS </strong>- <span class='escrText'>[2025] 5 S.C.R. 653</span><span class='ncDisplay'>2025 INSC 623</span><input type='hidden' id='cnr' value=ESCR010004192025></button></font><br><strong>Coram : VIKRAM NATH<sup style=\"color: #268e97;font-size: 22px;top: 0;\" class=\"tooltip-sup\" data-tooltip=\"Author\">*</sup>, SANDEEP MEHTA</strong><br> Issue for Consideration Whether the denial of admission to the appellant in the MBBS UG course under Scheduled Castes PwBD quota was grossly illegal, arbitrary and violative of the appellant&rsquo;s fundamental rights as guaranteed u/Arts.14 and 16 of the Constitution of India. Headnotes&dagger; course &ndash; Person with benchmark disabilities &ndash; The appellant being a person with benchmark disabilities (PwBD) belongs to the reserved category of Scheduled Caste was denied admission to the MBBS UG course despite standing high in merit in his category owing to his disability &ndash;<br><strong class='caseDetailsTD' ><span style='color:#212F3D' > Decision Date :</span><font color='green'> 02-05-2025</font><span style='color:#212F3D' > | Case No :</span><font color='green'> CIVIL APPEAL No. 5836/2025</font><span style='color:#212F3D' > | Disposal Nature :</span><font color='green'> Appeal(s) allowed</font>   <span style='color:#212F3D' > |  Bench :</span><font color='green'> 2 Judges</font></strong><div class='row my-1 mt-2 border bg-light'><div class='col-auto'><a href='#' class='btn btn-outline-secondary btn-sm my-1' onclick=open_splitview('4','2025','2025_5_653_666','2025INSC623','S')><i <i class='fas fa-columns me-2'></i>Split view</a></div><d